1. Product Perspective

CookSnap is a standalone, web-based application designed to recommend recipes based on grocery images provided by users. 
The system can be accessed through web browsers or mobile devices. It operates independently and does not integrate with online grocery platforms. 
CookSnap functions as a decision-support tool to assist users in meal planning using available ingredients.

2. Product Functions

The major functions of the CookSnap system include:

Uploading images of available groceries

Automatic detection of ingredients using image recognition

Recommendation of suitable recipes based on detected ingredients

Display of recipe details including preparation steps

Basic filtering of recipes (e.g., vegetarian / non-vegetarian)

User authentication and basic system monitoring

3. User Characteristics

End Users (Home Cooks, Students, Working Professionals):
Basic familiarity with smartphones or web applications.

System Administrators:
Basic knowledge of managing user access and monitoring system usage.

Developers / Maintainers:
Technical knowledge of web applications, databases, and AI models.

4. Constraints

The system requires a stable internet connection for image processing and recipe retrieval.

Accuracy of ingredient detection depends on image quality and dataset limitations.

The system is limited to recipe recommendation and does not provide dietary or medical advice.

Performance is dependent on server resources and model efficiency.
